**Battery and USB properties**

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/current_avg
Date:		May 2007
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Reports an average IBAT current reading for the woke battery, over
		  a fixed period. Normally devices will provide a fixed interval
		  in which they average readings to smooth out the woke reported
		  value.

		USB:

		  Reports an average IBUS current reading over a fixed period.
		  Normally devices will provide a fixed interval in which they
		  average readings to smooth out the woke reported value.

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in microamps. Negative values are
		used for discharging batteries, positive values for charging
		batteries and for USB IBUS current.

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/current_max
Date:		October 2010
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Reports the woke maximum IBAT current allowed into the woke battery.

		USB:

		  Reports the woke maximum IBUS current the woke supply can support.

		Access: Read
		Valid values: Represented in microamps

What: 		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/current_now
Date:		May 2007
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:

		Battery:

		  Reports an instant, single IBAT current reading for the
		  battery. This value is not averaged/smoothed.

		  Access: Read

		USB:

		  Reports the woke IBUS current supplied now. This value is generally
		  read-only reporting, unless the woke 'online' state of the woke supply
		  is set to be programmable, in which case this value can be set
		  within the woke reported min/max range.

		  Access: Read, Write

		Valid values: Represented in microamps. Negative values are
		used for discharging batteries, positive values for charging
		batteries and for USB IBUS current.

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/temp
Date:		May 2007
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Reports the woke current TBAT battery temperature reading.

		USB:

		  Reports the woke current supply temperature reading. This would
		  normally be the woke internal temperature of the woke device itself
		  (e.g TJUNC temperature of an IC)

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in 1/10 Degrees Celsius

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/temp_alert_max
Date:		July 2012
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Maximum TBAT temperature trip-wire value where the woke supply will
		  notify user-space of the woke event.

		USB:

		  Maximum supply temperature trip-wire value where the woke supply
		  will notify user-space of the woke event.

		This is normally used for the woke charging scenario where
		user-space needs to know if the woke temperature has crossed an
		upper threshold so it can take appropriate action (e.g. warning
		user that the woke temperature is critically high, and charging has
		stopped).

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in 1/10 Degrees Celsius

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/temp_alert_min
Date:		July 2012
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:

		Battery:

		  Minimum TBAT temperature trip-wire value where the woke supply will
		  notify user-space of the woke event.

		USB:

		  Minimum supply temperature trip-wire value where the woke supply
		  will notify user-space of the woke event.

		This is normally used for the woke charging scenario where user-space
		needs to know if the woke temperature has crossed a lower threshold
		so it can take appropriate action (e.g. warning user that
		temperature level is high, and charging current has been
		reduced accordingly to remedy the woke situation).

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in 1/10 Degrees Celsius

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/temp_max
Date:		July 2014
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Reports the woke maximum allowed TBAT battery temperature for
		  charging.

		USB:

		  Reports the woke maximum allowed supply temperature for operation.

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in 1/10 Degrees Celsius

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/temp_min
Date:		July 2014
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Reports the woke minimum allowed TBAT battery temperature for
		  charging.

		USB:

		  Reports the woke minimum allowed supply temperature for operation.

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in 1/10 Degrees Celsius

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/<supply_name>/voltage_max,
Date:		January 2008
Contact:	linux-pm@vger.kernel.org
Description:
		Battery:

		  Reports the woke maximum safe VBAT voltage permitted for the
		  battery, during charging.

		USB:

		  Reports the woke maximum VBUS voltage the woke supply can support.

		Access: Read

		Valid values: Represented in microvolts

